data.description: *IMPROVED PRICE! MOTIVATED SELLER!*  Highly desirable Kingswood home. This neighborhood backs up to and connects with Suburban Heights for easy access to NW 43rd St or NW 8th Ave. Centrally located in the heart of Gainesville. Just minutes from North Florida Hospital, Oaks Mall, Santa Fe College, The University of Florida, and is walking distance to Cofrin Nature Park. This home has 4 bedrooms, 3 baths, and a bonus room. One of the bedrooms can be utilized as an in-law suite or can provide an opportunity for a private room rental since it has its own private entrance. Upon entering the home, you will find a large open concept living area with a kitchen, living space, and dining area. There are double doors leading into a large bonus room that would be perfect for an office or a den. The split floorplan has 3 bedrooms and 2 baths on one side of the home, and the in-law suite on the opposite side. The in-law quarters has private access and its own bathroom and two closets. The kitchen has been renovated with new cabinets, stainless steel appliances, granite counter tops, and an island in the center for extra storage and seating. The home has an interior laundry space with an additional nook for storage and a door leading out to the backyard. The one car, oversized garage, is wonderful for extra storage or a work bench. Double sliding glass doors add to an open-feel off of the main living area and leads to the screened in back-porch. Perfect to enjoy your morning coffee! Beyond the covered porch is a spacious backyard with a wooden privacy fence. The backyard also features a fire pit and a paved area for additional seating. Finally, the home resides on a 0.38 acre corner lot with beautiful landscaping surrounding the home. This home is in such a prime neighborhood surrounded by other custom homes, mature trees, and sidewalks for your evening stroll.
